  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Isaiah’s Commission"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "In the year that King Uzziah died, I saw the Lord seated on a throne, high and exalted; and the train of His robe",
          {
            "noteId": 2523
          },
          "filled the temple."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "Above Him stood seraphim, each having six wings: With two wings they covered their faces, with two they covered their feet, and with two they were flying."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "And they were calling out to one another:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Holy, holy, holy is the LORD of Hosts;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the earth is full of His glory.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "At the sound of their voices the doorposts and thresholds shook, and the temple was filled with smoke."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Then I said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Woe is me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for I am ruined,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because I am a man of unclean lips",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "dwelling among a people of unclean lips;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for my eyes have seen the King,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD of Hosts.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "Then one of the seraphim flew to me, and in his hand was a glowing coal that he had taken with tongs from the altar."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "And with it he touched my mouth and said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Now that this has touched your lips,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your iniquity is removed",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and your sin is atoned for.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "Then I heard the voice of the Lord saying:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Whom shall I send?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will go for Us?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "And I said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Here am I. Send me!”",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "And He replied:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Go and tell this people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Be ever hearing, but never understanding;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "be ever seeing, but never perceiving.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2524
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the hearts of this people calloused;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "deafen their ears and close their eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Otherwise they might see with their eyes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "hear with their ears,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "understand with their hearts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and turn and be healed.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2525
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Then I asked:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“How long, O Lord?”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "And He replied:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Until the cities lie ruined",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and without inhabitant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until the houses are left unoccupied",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the land is desolate and ravaged,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "until the LORD has driven men far away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the land is utterly forsaken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And though a tenth remains in the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will be burned again.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "As the terebinth and oak leave stumps when felled,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the holy seed will be a stump in the land.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
